title: Habyt Novena (Previously Hotel Balestier)
name: Duan
text:
‚ÄúTropical Wilderness Survival: Couples‚Äô Special Edition‚Äù

If your girlfriend has long, beautiful hair and you want to give her a truly unforgettable travel experience, this hotel will not disappoint.

First, the hotel‚Äôs amenities are a masterpiece of contrast‚Äîthe kitchen is fully stocked with pots and pans, as if inviting me to become a gourmet chef, yet somehow, there is no hairdryer. So, my girlfriend had no choice but to dry her long hair using my tiny handheld portable fan‚Äîyes, the kind designed to provide a gentle breeze while waiting in line outdoors. The scene was tragic yet hilarious: she sat there, painstakingly directing the weak airflow at her soaking wet hair, moving millimeter by millimeter in sheer determination. The process lasted over an hour, making me wonder if I should just manually fan her myself. This hotel truly embraces minimalist living‚Äîafter all, who said drying your hair is a basic hotel necessity?

Second, the check-in process felt like an escape room, but in expert mode, with no hints provided. We had booked two nights, yet we couldn‚Äôt even get in on the first night. The front desk closes ridiculously early, and the hotel provides zero staff to assist guests. Instead, they leave you with one cryptic email. Our challenge? Decode the email and figure out how to check in‚Äîall by ourselves. Didn‚Äôt see the email? Congratulations, you‚Äôve just unlocked nightmare mode!

We landed in Singapore at 10 PM, excited to check in, only to find the hotel entrance completely locked and lifeless‚Äîas if it had been abandoned for years. No staff, no instructions, just us standing there with our suitcases like contestants in a survival reality show. We tried calling, messaging, even searching for a hidden entrance‚Äînothing. After sweating in Singapore‚Äôs humid night until 1 AM, we finally gave up and booked another hotel. By the time we managed to check in for the second night, our enthusiasm had already been completely drained. At this point, I‚Äôm convinced the hotel‚Äôs business model isn‚Äôt about providing accommodation‚Äîit‚Äôs about offering a mystery-solving survival challenge.

Finally, when we politely requested a refund for the night we never even stayed, the hotel‚Äôs attitude remained as unshakable as a medieval fortress. Their philosophy seems to be: ‚ÄúWhether you stay or not is your problem. Keeping your money is ours.‚Äù

In summary: if you want to test your girlfriend‚Äôs patience, challenge your own ability to calm her fury in extreme heat, and experience a hardcore escape room + extreme outdoor survival combo, then this is the perfect hotel for you! It‚Äôs guaranteed to either bring you closer together‚Äîor straight to a breakup.
responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Letian,

Thank you for sharing your experience, and we‚Äôre truly sorry that your stay didn't meet expectations. We can imagine how frustrating it must have been dealing with the challenges you described, especially after a late arrival. Our goal is to make our guests feel comfortable and welcome, and we certainly don‚Äôt want anyone to feel stranded or frustrated. We appreciate your feedback on the amenities, check-in process, and communication‚Äîwe‚Äôll review these areas to ensure future guests don‚Äôt face the same issues. We're sorry for any inconvenience caused, and we hope you'll reconsider giving us another chance in the future. Thanks again for bringing these points to our attention.

Warmest regards

title: Rejoy Suites (Confinement Centre)
name: EL Loh
text:
‚ÄúI recently had the pleasure of staying at Re'Joy Suites following the birth of my baby, and I can confidently say it was one of the best decisions I made during this transition into motherhood.

From the moment I walked in, I was greeted by friendly staff who made me feel at home. The center itself is beautifully designed‚Äîbright, airy, and impeccably clean, creating a serene atmosphere that was perfect for recovery. Each room was equipped with all the essentials, ensuring that both my baby and I had everything we needed for comfort and care.

One of the standout aspects of name Shirley was the level of personalized care I received. The nurses and caregivers were not only highly skilled but also incredibly compassionate. They took the time to understand my individual needs and preferences, providing tailored advice on breastfeeding, infant care, and postpartum recovery. Their encouragement made a world of difference during those initial challenging days.

The meals provided were another highlight. The center offered a delicious and nutritious menu, specifically designed to support postpartum healing and lactation. I appreciated the variety and how they catered to my dietary preferences, ensuring that I was well-nourished while adjusting to motherhood.

The range of activities available was impressive as well. Daily workshops on topics like baby massage, breastfeeding techniques, and self-care were incredibly beneficial. These sessions not only provided valuable information but also fostered a sense of community among the new parents. I made some wonderful connections and found comfort in sharing experiences with others going through similar challenges.

The environment at Re'Joy Suites felt safe and nurturing. The staff was always available, whether it was for a late-night question about my baby or a simple chat during the day. They were genuinely invested in my well-being and that of my baby, which made the experience all the more reassuring.

Overall, my time at Re'Joy Suites  was transformative. It provided me with the support, knowledge, and confidence I needed as a new mother. I left feeling empowered and more connected to my baby, ready to take on the challenges ahead. I highly recommend this confinement center to any new parent looking for a supportive and enriching environment during such a pivotal time in their life. Thank you, Re'Joy Suites for making my postpartum experience so positive!‚Äù

title: Ivins Peranakan Restaurant (Heartland Mall Kovan)
name: Janice Lee
text:
I had actually been to Ivins before, about 7 years ago. I remember I like the burst of flavours in the nonya food. So when I pass by this restaurant again, I want to enjoy the food here again, this time trying the food of my choices. And yes, I enjoy this second outing at here so much more because I love the all food items I ordered and the service is very good now.

The food here features a rich medley of bold flavours that excites the tastebuds and soft, distinctive Southeast Asian flavours as base notes that give the food an extra oomph and a taste of nostalgia and heritage.

The place is like a humble little restaurant that is always full house at peak hours. I like the pottery and tin boxes, painted with florals in earthy or pastel colours, on display on shelves. It gives that kind of homely Peranakan feel.

The service is such a huge, huge improvement from that of the last visit 7 years ago. The young service staffs are friendly, prompt to respond and thoughtful. Now I am eager to pop back right in whenever I pass by this place.

Sotong Assam Puteh Squid served in a lemongrass tamarind gravy looks unassuming but the taste will excite the senses with the aroma of spices, tangy taste of tamarind, The squid rings are tender and have this milky brininess that is complemented by the tamarind.

Nonya Mee Siam is the best Mee Siam. Spicy vemicelli is full of goodlies, with prawns, beancurd and egg, soaked in a tangy tamarind sauce. Refreshing, nutty and creamy at the same time.

Gula Melaka Sago features bouncy juicy sago that I love.

Bandung with Chin Chow is sweet, floral and refreshing 👍🏻

Thoughts: Great Place to enjoy Peranakan food

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: Jim Colico
text:
You’ve missed Singapore if you haven’t seen it from the Marina Bay Sands SkyPark Observation Deck.
Here's a little trick:
Instead of paying S$23 (adult) and S$17 (children) admission fees, buy a ticket going to CÉ LA VI. It is a rooftop nightclub at MBS and this offers an entry voucher for only S$20 with fully redeemable food and beverage purchases in the bar.
Availing this voucher will be the bang for your buck since the bar is also located on the observation deck. From the bar, you’ll be all awe-struck with jaws dropped as you drink in the panoramic vistas of the stunning Marina Bay, the world-class cityscape, the architectural wonders of Supertree Grove, and the vibrant colors of Gardens by the Bay.

title: SkyPark Observation Deck

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: Sharon LIMTL (AlphaOmega_Life)
text:
Marina Bay Sands is one of the most luxurious properties owned by Singapore, and besides the hotel, there are many interesting places to visit. One of them is Marina Bay Sands Skypark, perfect for exciting visits with friends.
Above 57 levels, you can see various tourist attractions such as Gardens by the Bay and Supertree Grove, and the streets that stretch along the Singapore Strait. You can also enjoy the city skyline from above - the bustling city of Singapore looks amazing when you're 200 meters above the ground. Remember to capture this moment with your friends!

Address: 10 Bayfront Avenue, Singapore 018956

Opening Hours: Daily: 11am – 9pm
Opening hours may vary on special dates.
Visitors typically spend 45 min – 1 hr here.
Last entry into the Skypark Observation Deck will be at 8.30pm.

Price: From $20

Top of Singapore "

The Marina Bay Sands SkyPark is a roof like no other, perched 200 metres in the air featuring an infinity pool and observation deck.
looks like a celestial surfboard or a spaceship docking on a tripod. No matter where your imagination takes you, It is a wondrous feat of engineering.

Designed by visionary architect Moshe Safdie,

Dine at LAVO Italian Restaurant & Rooftop Bar or savour a cocktail at CÉ LA VI—located atop the Sands SkyPark—and witness an unforgettable panoramic view of the Singapore skyline.

Opening hours

Last ticket sales at 8.30pm (last entry at 8.50pm)

منظر جميل ويستاهل الزياره
احلى وقت الساعه 5 العصر
textTranslated:
Beautiful view and worth a visit
The best time is 5 pm

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: Cole Humphreys
text: Awesome view of the city. One side you can see the ocean and all the gardens. On the other you can see the unique architecture of Singapore.  Loss of one star because you have to pay to go up there if you are not a guest of the hotel.

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: Abdul Grosir Mukena
text: Wonderful view. Worth in every penny.

title: Bef Jurong Hill
name: varun wakarekar
text: Good place to hangout. Nice view

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: abdulrahman alhussain
text:
Seamless experience! Stunning views of Singapore! The check in experience is very quick and efficient! It is located on the 57th floor of the Marina bay hotel! Very crowded at the top but still a lot of space available for pictures and for roaming around.

Nice experience! Will recommend to anyone visiting Singapore!

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: Daniel Montes
text: What a awesome place. You should visit this place

title: Tanjong Beach
name: Kelvin Martinez-Arreola
text: Very nice when its not crowded.

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: Gautam Maniar
text: Amazing view of Singapore from top should see both in daylight and at night

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: John Warhurst
text:
Great city views.
Drinks are pricey but worth it for the experience.

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: KONGDET L
text: Good atmosphere, beautiful corner

title: Bef Jurong Hill
name: Shiori Kawahara
text:
2019.7.21に初めて行った時の動画を今頃投稿します😆✨

この頃のバードパークはジュロンにありました。

話が上手なお姉さんとオウムのショーと、なかなか動かないキモかわいいハシビロコウが印象的でとても楽しかった思い出です🥰

よーし！
次は新しくオープンしたバードパークへ行ってきます😆💓
textTranslated:
I'm posting a video from my first visit on 2019.7.21😆✨

The bird park was in Jurong at the time.

The talkative lady and the parrot show, and the cute but creepy shoebill that didn't move much were impressive and were a lot of fun memories🥰

Okay!
Next, I'm going to the newly opened bird park😆💓

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: Anurag Gawande
text: A must go place. Mind blowing view you will get to see.

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: Simon Schneider
text: The view is definitely nice, I'm just annoyed because we were looking forward to spend an amazing night at the rooftop bar and while the official website says "Are reservations required to enter CÉ LA VI Club Lounge? Reservations are not required", we were then told at the entry that by default a reservation is always required. On the Sky deck you could see that at least half the restaurant and bar area was empty.

title: Mount Faber Park
name: Andrea Casadei
text: Bel posto per una vista dall alto della città. Punto di partenza per la cable car x Sentosa.
textTranslated: Nice place for a bird's eye view of the city. Starting point for the cable car x Sentosa.

title: Henderson Waves
name: Chuc Nguyen
text: A Nice place; no entrance fee for whoever love nature

title: Henderson Waves
name: Mudasirhabib
text: Very beautiful spot, for better view you should visit during night

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: Byron Li
text: A little pricy but if it's your first time in Singapore and want to see the city skylines might be worth it. I do advise going at night tho it gets really hot in the day. Plus there are light shows at 7, 8 and 9 PM

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: Tuyet V
text: The attraction has a nice view of the city and partial ocean view. It was nice to go right  before sunset and stayed till the sky is dark.

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: Adarsh Ajith
text: Stunning view from the Top..best time to visit is around sunset.

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: K D M
text:
Very good view. Busy but nice.
You can cheaper tickets at discount sites such as Klook or GetYourGuide depending on the day

title: SkyPark Observation Deck
name: Dylan E
text: Wonderful view of the gardens and surrounding city. However, the entrance fee is quite steep at $23 and once at the top there is little to do except take photos.

title: Henderson Waves
name: Wong Wendell
text: Grand bridge. Good for photos from afar. Too much algae close up.

title: Mount Faber Station
name: Adarsh Ajith
text: Very good Experience...Good view of the City
